  "prompt": "How we save a language from extinction?",
  "response": "To save a language from extinction, several strategies can be employed:\n\n1. Documentation and Preservation\n- Record spoken language\n- Create comprehensive dictionaries\n- Develop grammar books\n- Digitize existing materials\n\n2. Education and Language Transmission\n- Teach language in schools\n- Create immersion programs\n- Develop bilingual education\n- Encourage intergenerational learning\n\n3. Community Engagement\n- Support native speaker communities\n- Organize language workshops\n- Create cultural events\n- Promote language pride and identity\n\n4. Modern Technology\n- Develop language learning apps\n- Create online resources\n- Use social media platforms\n- Produce digital content\n\n5. Government and Institutional Support\n- Implement language protection policies\n- Provide funding for language programs\n- Recognize language as official/cultural heritage\n- Support linguistic research\n\n6. Cultural Revival\n- Integrate language in cultural practices\n- Promote traditional music and storytelling\n- Create media content in native language\n- Celebrate linguistic diversity\n\n7. Academic Research\n- Conduct linguistic studies\n- Train language specialists\n- Support academic research programs\n- Develop comprehensive language documentation\n\n8. International Collaboration\n- Share best practices\n- Support global language preservation efforts\n- Collaborate with linguistic organizations\n\nSuccessful language preservation requires sustained, multi-faceted efforts from communities, governments, and institutions.",
